message: “The Racine Dominican Sisters and associates support human rights by opposing the trafficking of women, children and men for sexual exploitation and international works of enslavement. We commit our prayer, study, resources and action to end this criminal activity against our sisters and brothers.”

data.description: RACINE COUNTY — Last month, the U.S. House of Representatives passed a series of bills in support of efforts to combat human trafficking.
data.title: Racine Dominicans continue to fight human trafficking
